# .windsurfrules — TavernKeep Development Guidelines

These rules govern all AI-assisted code generation in this project. Follow them precisely on every file creation, edit, or refactor.

---

## 1. Project Identity

- **App name**: TavernKeep
- **Purpose**: D&D shop management and sharing platform for DMs and players
- **Stack**: Next.js 14 (App Router) · TypeScript · Tailwind CSS · shadcn/ui · Supabase · OpenAI API · Google Stitch (design) · Vercel

---

## 2. Google Stitch Design Workflow (ALWAYS DO THIS FIRST)

Before writing any UI code for a screen or component:

1. Use the Stitch MCP to list available projects and screens
2. Fetch the Design DNA for the relevant screen (fonts, colors, spacing, layout)
3. Retrieve the screen's HTML as a pixel-perfect reference
4. If this is the first screen built, generate a `DESIGN.md` in the project root containing all extracted design tokens — colors, typography, spacing scale, border radii, shadows
5. Implement the component in React + Tailwind, matching the Stitch design exactly

**If no Stitch screen exists for a view**, use the design tokens already in `DESIGN.md` and the aesthetic direction in the prompt. Never invent new colors, fonts, or spacing — always anchor to the established system.

`DESIGN.md` is auto-generated from Stitch — never hand-edit it. It is the single source of truth for the design system.

---

## 3. TypeScript Rules

- **Strict mode always on**. No `any`. No `@ts-ignore` unless absolutely unavoidable and documented.
- All props interfaces named `[ComponentName]Props`
- All DB row types live in `/types/database.ts` as exported interfaces
- All API request/response bodies validated with `zod` schemas in `/lib/validators/`
- Use `type` for unions/intersections; use `interface` for object shapes

```typescript
// ✅ Good
interface ShopCardProps {
  shop: Shop;
  onEdit?: (id: string) => void;
}

// ❌ Bad
const ShopCard = ({ shop, onEdit }: any) => { ... }
```

---

## 4. File and Folder Structure

```
/app
  /(auth)/           → Auth pages (login, callback)
  /(dm)/             → DM-protected pages
  /(player)/         → Public player pages
  /api/              → API route handlers
/components
  /ui/               → shadcn/ui primitives (never modify these directly)
  /dm/               → DM-specific components
  /player/           → Player-specific components
  /shared/           → Components used in both contexts
/lib
  /supabase/         → Supabase client helpers (server.ts, client.ts, middleware.ts)
  /prompts/          → All AI prompt strings as named exports
  /validators/       → Zod schemas
  /utils/            → Pure utility functions
  /constants/        → App-wide constants (enums, config values)
/types
  /database.ts       → DB row interfaces
  /index.ts          → Re-exports
/hooks               → Custom React hooks
/public              → Static assets
/supabase
  /migrations/       → All schema migrations
DESIGN.md            → Stitch-extracted design tokens (auto-generated, do not hand-edit)
```

- One component per file
- File names: `kebab-case.tsx` for components, `camelCase.ts` for utilities

