## 6. Data Fetching Rules

- Server-side data fetching via `createServerClient` from `@supabase/ssr`
- Client-side mutations via Supabase browser client in custom hooks
- All Supabase queries handle errors explicitly — never assume success
- Realtime subscriptions set up in Client Components in `useEffect` with cleanup

```typescript
// ✅ Always handle errors
const { data: shop, error } = await supabase
  .from('shops')
  .select('*')
  .eq('slug', slug)
  .single();

if (error) throw new Error(`Failed to load shop: ${error.message}`);
```

---

## 7. API Route Rules

- All routes in `/app/api/` using Next.js Route Handlers
- Validate all inputs with Zod before processing
- Consistent response shape:
  ```typescript
  { data: T, error: null }                        // success
  { data: null, error: { message: string } }      // failure
  ```
- **Player-facing routes MUST strip `is_hidden = true` items before returning** — enforced at API level, not the UI
- DM routes MUST verify `session.user.id` ownership before any write
- AI routes rate-limited to 5 requests/min per IP
- `OPENAI_API_KEY` is server-side only — never referenced in client components

---

## 8. Database & Supabase Rules

- RLS enabled on every table — policies written before any data access code
- Only the **anon key** (`NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`) is used — there is no service role key
- All RLS policies enforce that DMs can only access their own campaigns and shops
- Use `npx supabase` for all CLI commands — no global install
- All schema changes go through migrations in `/supabase/migrations/` — never alter tables in the dashboard
- Soft-delete items with `deleted_at timestamp` — never hard delete inventory
- All timestamps in UTC

---

## 9. Authentication Rules

- Google OAuth only via Supabase Auth
- **Google OAuth is deferred until a Vercel deployment URL exists.** Scaffold and wire it up with clear comments, but do not block other features.
- When Google OAuth is activated: Supabase callback URL = `https://[your-project].supabase.co/auth/v1/callback`
- Auth state checked in `middleware.ts` for all `/dm/*` and `/api/dm/*` routes
- Player routes are fully public — zero auth required
- Never store session data in localStorage — use httpOnly cookies via `@supabase/ssr`

---

## 10. AI Integration Rules

All AI prompt strings live in `/lib/prompts/` as named exports. Never write prompts inline.

```typescript
// /lib/prompts/itemGeneration.ts
export const buildItemGenerationPrompt = (context: ItemGenerationContext): string => `
You are a D&D 5e item generator. Return only valid JSON...
`;
```

- Use **GPT-4o** for all text generation (items, shopkeeper profiles)
- Use **DALL-E 3** for all image generation (keeper portrait, exterior, interior)
- Always set `max_tokens` explicitly
- Always request JSON-only responses for structured data; parse with try/catch
- DALL-E 3 prompts must include: `"painterly fantasy illustration, warm candlelight, highly detailed, atmospheric"`
- Store all generated images in Supabase Storage — never regenerate unless DM explicitly requests
- Show loading skeletons during all AI generation calls
- Disable generation buttons while a call is in flight

